Overview
Unity3DChess is a 3D chess game developed as part of my university dissertation project using Unity. This repository contains the source code for the game, ready for you to download and explore! Dive into the world of chess with a polished and interactive 3D experience.

Features
3D Chess Gameplay: Enjoy the classic game of chess in a 3D environment.
Interactive Interface: Navigate through menus and play with intuitive controls.
Multiple Chess Piece Movements: Each piece follows standard chess rules for movement.
Seamless Scene Management: Easily open and explore saved scenes in Unity.
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Unity Hub installed on your machine.
Unity Editor version [Specify Version, e.g., 2022.1.0f1].
Installation
Clone the repository or download the ZIP file.
